name: Joe Watts
text: Small but beautiful piece of property that was once a working farm. Now owned by Auburn University, it has trails with access to a small creek, a building with rustic meeting rooms, beautiful views of Alabama's rolling hills and a very rural setting. Interesting location for bird watching as well as just getting back to nature.  Loggerhead Shrikes were easy to spot in the summer. A small bird feeder brought in lots of the usual suspects. Scissor-tailed Flycatchers are not far away, so could be at this location as well.
